  "logo": "https://miniodis-rproxy.lisn.upsaclay.fr/coda-v2-prod-public/logos/2026-06-03-1780513663/396055ccba31/logo.png?AWSAccessKeyId=codabench-prod&Signature=vfbNHXFucAHag5IzDQ1evQvHBLw%3D&Expires=1782128530",
  "logo_icon": "https://miniodis-rproxy.lisn.upsaclay.fr/coda-v2-prod-public/logos/2026-06-03-1780513663/396055ccba31/logo_icon.png?AWSAccessKeyId=codabench-prod&Signature=tYpuH1scktg2lA8d3m0exA0bERQ%3D&Expires=1782128530",
  "terms": "<h2>Terms and Conditions</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Data is released for research purposes under CC BY 4.0.</li>\n  <li>Teams may use any external data or pre-trained models.</li>\n  <li>Manual annotation of test instances is not permitted.</li>\n  <li>Each participating team must submit a system description paper to be included in the final rankings.</li>\n  <li>Test set gold labels must not be shared before the results announcement.</li>\n  <li>By participating, teams agree to allow their results to be published in the shared task overview paper.</li>\n</ul>",
  "pages": [
    {
      "id": 80565,
      "title": "overview",
      "content": "<h2>ImageEval2026 Subtask 2: CRAI-Bench: Cultural Accuracy Evaluation for Arabic Text-to-Image Generation</h2>\n<p>CRAI-Bench evaluates whether AI-generated images faithfully represent Qatari and Arab cultural scenes. Given a reference image, a caption, and an AI-generated image produced from that caption, participants predict CRAI scores across five cultural accuracy dimensions.</p>\n<h3>CRAI Formula</h3>\n<pre>CRAI = 0.30 × CEA + 0.20 × CC + 0.20 × CS + 0.20 × CI − 0.10 × HP</pre>\n<h3>Score Interpretation</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>0.85 – 1.00: Highly accurate</li>\n  <li>0.70 – 0.84: Mostly accurate</li>\n  <li>0.50 – 0.69: Moderately accurate</li>\n  <li>0.30 – 0.49: Weak</li>\n  <li>Below 0.30: Poor or misleading</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Contact</h3>\n<p> <a href=\"mailto:imageeval2026@gmail.com\">imageeval2026@gmail.com</a></p>",
      "index": 0
    },
    {
      "id": 80573,
      "title": "evaluation",
      "content": "<h2>Evaluation</h2>\n<p><strong>Primary metric:</strong> Spearman correlation between predicted and gold CRAI_composite scores. Higher is better.</p>\n<p><strong>Secondary metric:</strong> MAE on CRAI_composite. Lower is better. Used as tiebreaker.</p>\n<p>Per-dimension scores (CEA, CC, CS, CI, HP) are reported on the leaderboard for diagnostic purposes but do not affect ranking.</p>\n<h3>Organizer Baselines</h3>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n  <tr><th>System</th><th>Spearman</th><th>MAE</th></tr>\n  <tr><td>Mean baseline</td><td>N/A</td><td>0.3450</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>GPT-4 via OpenRouter</td><td>0.6250</td><td>0.2248</td></tr>\n</table>\n<h3>Submission Format</h3>\n<p>⚠️ Important:  Submit a zip file only containing <code>predictions.tsv</code> with these tab-separated columns:</p>\n<pre>id    CRAI_CEA    CRAI_CC    CRAI_CS    CRAI_CI    CRAI_HP    CRAI_composite</pre>\n<p>Rules:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>All scores must be floats in [0.0, 1.0]</li>\n  <li>Header row is required</li>\n  <li>All instances must be present</li>\n  <li>CRAI_composite must equal 0.30×CEA + 0.20×CC + 0.20×CS + 0.20×CI − 0.10×HP</li>\n</ul>",
      "index": 1
    },
    {
      "id": 80567,
      "title": "data",
      "content": "<h2>Data</h2>\n<p>The dataset consists of (reference image, caption, generated image) triples grounded in Qatari culture. Each of 40 reference images has 5 caption versions varying in cultural specificity from fully Qatari-specific (v1) to entirely generic (v5).</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n  <tr><th>Split</th><th>Images</th><th>Instances</th><th>Gold Labels</th></tr>\n  <tr><td>Train</td><td>24</td><td>120</td><td>Released</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>Dev</td><td>8</td><td>40</td><td>Released</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>Test</td><td>8</td><td>40</td><td>Hidden</td></tr>\n</table>\n<p>Download data and scripts from GitHub under Task 2: <a href=\"https://github.com/ImageEval2026/ImageEval2026-tasks\">https://github.com/ImageEval2026/ImageEval2026-tasks</a></p>",
      "index": 2
    }
  ],
